The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Tuesday, April 06, 2004 				 Drive to check Rajni damage 
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT RajnikanthChennai, April 5: The feuding between Rajnikanth fans and the PMK today took a serious turn with ally DMK seeking the Election Commissions intervention to prevent clashes like the one that erupted in Madurai recently.																								Two days ago, members of the Rajnikanth Fan Clubs Association had clashed with PMK members when they tried to wave black flags at party leader Ramadoss to protest his derogatory remarks against the Tamil superstar.																								DMK chief M. Karunanidhi called a meeting of all allies  the Congress, the PMK, the MDMK, the CPI, the CPM and the Indian Union Muslim League  after rumours last night that Jayalalithaas ADMK would get Ramadoss arrested near Erode.																								Earlier, the police had registered cases against him and other PMK volunteers, charging them with attempt to murder.																								Todays meeting accused the ruling ADMK of trying to incite violence at a time when Opposition parties have been going about their poll campaigns peacefully.																								It also condemned Jayalalithaas continued unrestrained personalised attack against Congress chief Sonia Gandhi.																								Assailing the polices partisan attitude, the DMK front wondered how they permitted waving of black flags at Ramadoss when he was campaigning in Madurai. 																								It said Left members who had planned to show Jayalalithaa black flags during her Thanjavur campaign had been arrested far away from the meeting venue.																								In a strongly-worded joint resolution, it asked how different yardsticks could be applied to different people.																								Claiming ADMK goons masquerading as Rajnikanth fans had directed the attack with the aid of the police, the DMK front alleged that this is a planned act of violence. 																								It warned its cadre and the people not to fall a prey to this evil design to scuttle our electoral victory.																								The resolution also urged the ADMK to withdraw the cases against Ramadoss and other PMK volunteers.																								Speaking to reporters, Karunanidhi declined comment on Rajnikanth fans being injured in the clash. But he said he was ready to talk to the actor.																								Asked if Rajnikanths decision on who to support in the elections would affect the DMK, Karunanidhi said: Even Rajnikanth will not want our alliances prospects to be affected. He then added the actor is a good man.																								On the BJP top leadership repeatedly asserting that Sonia Gandhis foreign origin was not a personal issue, he said: They have made it a political issue.
